</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 2  
</p>
<p><b>Annual report of the United Nations High Commissioner 
</b></p>
<p><b>for Human Rights and reports of the Office of the  
</b></p>
<p><b>High Commissioner and the Secretary-General 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Measures taken to implement Human Rights Council 
resolution 9/8 and obstacles to its implementation, including 
recommendations for further improving the effectiveness, 
harmonization and reform of  
the treaty body system 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Report of the Secretary-General 
</b></p>
<p> 
United Nations A/HRC/29/53 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>General Assembly </b>Distr.: General 
6 May 2015 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Original: English<b> </b></p>


<p>1. In its resolution 9/8, the Human Rights Council requested the Secretary-General to 
</p>
<p>report annually to the Council on measures taken to implement resolution 9/8 and on 
</p>
<p>obstacles to its implementation, including recommendations for further improving the 
</p>
<p>effectiveness of, harmonizing and reforming the treaty body system. The present report is 
</p>
<p>submitted pursuant to that request. 
</p>
<p>2. In its resolution 68/268, the General Assembly requested the Secretary-General to 
</p>
<p>present to the Assembly, on a biennial basis, a comprehensive report on the status of the 
</p>
<p>treaty body system and the progress achieved by the treaty bodies in achieving greater 
</p>
<p>efficiency and effectiveness in their work, including the number of reports submitted and 
</p>
<p>reviewed by the committees, the visits undertaken and the individual communications 
</p>
<p>received and reviewed, where applicable, the state of the backlog, capacity-building efforts 
</p>
<p>and results achieved, as well as the situation in terms of ratifications, increased reporting 
</p>
<p>and the allocation of meeting time and proposals on measures, including on the basis of 
</p>
<p>information and observations from Member States, to enhance the engagement of all State 
</p>
<p>parties in the dialogue with the treaty bodies. The first report of the Secretary-General 
</p>
<p>prepared pursuant to resolution 68/268 will be submitted to the Assembly in 2016. 
</p>
<p>3. In the light of the overlapping reporting obligations, the report of the Secretary-
</p>
<p>General prepared pursuant to Human Rights Council resolution 9/8 was postponed from the 
</p>
<p>twenty-eighth session of the Council to the twenty-ninth (see A/HRC/28/21). 
</p>
<p>4. Comprehensive information on the topics raised in Human Rights Council resolution 
</p>
<p>9/8 is available at the following websites: 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Ratification status by country or by treaty: 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/TreatyBodyExternal/Treaty.aspx 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Status of ratification maps: 
</p>
<p>http://indicators.ohchr.org/ 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Reporting status to human rights treaty body: 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/TreatyBodyExternal/Countries.aspx 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Timely, late and non-reporting to human rights treaty bodies: 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/TreatyBodyExternal/LateReporting.aspx 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Calendar of country reviews by treaty bodies: 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/TreatyBodyExternal/MasterCalendar.aspx 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Common core documents: 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/TreatyBodyExternal/CoreDocuments.aspx 
</p>
<p>&#8226; Treaty body database (search engine for treaty body documentation): 
</p>
<p>http://tbinternet.ohchr.org/_layouts/treatybodyexternal/TBSearch.aspx 
</p>
